<item>
            <title>[LU-9144] kernel update [RHEL6.8 2.6.32-642.13.2.el6]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9144</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Security Fix(es):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A use-after-free flaw was found in the way the Linux kernel&apos;s Datagram&lt;br/&gt;
Congestion Control Protocol (DCCP) implementation freed SKB (socket buffer)&lt;br/&gt;
resources for a DCCP_PKT_REQUEST packet when the IPV6_RECVPKTINFO option is set&lt;br/&gt;
on the socket. A local, unprivileged user could use this flaw to alter the&lt;br/&gt;
kernel memory, allowing them to escalate their privileges on the system.&lt;br/&gt;
(CVE-2017-6074, Important)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Bugs fixed (&lt;a href=&quot;https://bugzilla.redhat.com/):&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugzilla.redhat.com/):&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1423071 - CVE-2017-6074 kernel: use after free in dccp protocol&lt;/p&gt;</description>
